1
00:00:05,516 --> 00:00:10,561
Subtitles by explosiveskull
www.OpenSubtitles.org

2
00:00:52,854 --> 00:00:54,200
I'm telling you, Addie,

3
00:00:54,222 --> 00:00:56,235
if we build these factories
in San Miguel,

4
00:00:56,258 --> 00:00:58,439
the business is going
through the roof.

5
00:00:58,460 --> 00:01:01,542
<i>I'd rather have you
than the money.</i>

6
00:01:01,563 --> 00:01:04,378
<i>You're away too much, Slade,
and I...</i>

7
00:01:06,502 --> 00:01:07,548
<i>You okay?</i>

8
00:01:09,070 --> 00:01:11,884
When you're home,
when we're all together,

9
00:01:11,906 --> 00:01:14,020
I never even think about it.

10
00:01:14,042 --> 00:01:16,155
But as soon as you're away, I...

11
00:01:27,656 --> 00:01:30,903
For God's sake, Addie,
Cambodia was years ago.

12
00:01:30,925 --> 00:01:32,840
Before we were even married.

13
00:01:32,860 --> 00:01:34,408
<i>We were in love.</i>

14
00:01:34,430 --> 00:01:36,310
<i>We were engaged.</i>

15
00:01:36,332 --> 00:01:38,010
And we've both
seen enough combat

16
00:01:38,032 --> 00:01:40,279
to know that however much
wounds may heal...

17
00:01:42,203 --> 00:01:44,016
How could you do this to me?

18
00:01:44,038 --> 00:01:45,386
I trusted you.

19
00:01:52,113 --> 00:01:53,960
<i>...the scars never go away.</i>

20
00:01:55,751 --> 00:01:56,797
Can I talk to him?

21
00:01:56,819 --> 00:01:59,232
I know. I know.

22
00:01:59,254 --> 00:02:02,469
And I swear to you, Addie,
I haven't lied to you since.

23
00:02:02,491 --> 00:02:04,405
And I will never
lie to you again.

24
00:02:05,159 --> 00:02:06,507
You believe me, don't you?

25
00:02:07,095 --> 00:02:08,241
Of course I do.

26
00:02:08,263 --> 00:02:09,976
- It's just...
- Can I talk?

27
00:02:11,467 --> 00:02:13,414
<i>Somebody wants you.</i>

28
00:02:13,435 --> 00:02:15,716
- I wonder who.
<i>- Hi, Papa.</i>

29
00:02:15,738 --> 00:02:17,418
Hey, buddy. Teeth all brushed?

30
00:02:17,872 --> 00:02:18,985
Yeah.

31
00:02:20,676 --> 00:02:21,662
Read to me.

32
00:02:21,677 --> 00:02:22,922
I would, Joe,

33
00:02:22,944 --> 00:02:24,398
but I'm late for
a dinner meeting and...

34
00:02:24,413 --> 00:02:25,626
Just a little.

35
00:02:27,483 --> 00:02:28,513
A little little.

36
00:02:28,883 --> 00:02:29,996
Hmm?

37
00:02:36,325 --> 00:02:39,172
<i>"The land
was filled with dragons"</i>

38
00:02:39,193 --> 00:02:40,741
<i>and the people were afraid.</i>

39
00:02:40,763 --> 00:02:43,310
<i>But the Shining Knight
came riding forth</i>

40
00:02:43,332 --> 00:02:45,746
<i>to protect both man and maid.</i>

41
00:02:45,768 --> 00:02:50,016
<i>He faced the fiercest creatures
that the world had ever known.</i>

42
00:02:50,037 --> 00:02:51,984
<i>And he did it without any help.</i>

43
00:02:52,006 --> 00:02:53,720
<i>He did it all alone.</i>

44
00:02:53,742 --> 00:02:58,057
<i>And when his work was done,
the dragons were no more.</i>

45
00:02:58,079 --> 00:03:00,360
<i>And so the Knight rode on,</i>

46
00:03:00,382 --> 00:03:03,363
<i>"into legend, into lore."</i>

47
00:03:04,353 --> 00:03:05,998
<i>And that's it for tonight, kid.</i>

48
00:03:06,020 --> 00:03:08,100
More. Please?

49
00:03:08,122 --> 00:03:09,969
<i>I've gotta go, buddy,</i>

50
00:03:09,991 --> 00:03:11,738
<i>and you've gotta get to sleep.</i>

51
00:03:11,760 --> 00:03:12,790
Okay.

52
00:03:15,597 --> 00:03:16,677
He misses you.

53
00:03:17,533 --> 00:03:19,145
<i>We miss you.</i>

54
00:03:19,167 --> 00:03:21,080
I'll be on the last plane
out tonight.

55
00:03:22,671 --> 00:03:24,751
I love you, Adeline Wilson.

56
00:03:24,773 --> 00:03:27,688
And I adore you, Slade Wilson.

57
00:03:42,925 --> 00:03:44,438
Under the covers,
little soldier.

58
00:03:44,460 --> 00:03:46,172
Aye-aye, Captain.

59
00:03:47,463 --> 00:03:48,509
Read to me, Mama.

60
00:03:48,530 --> 00:03:50,744
- But Papa already read you...
- Please?

61
00:03:50,766 --> 00:03:54,681
Don't give me that wide-eyed
innocent routine, mister.

62
00:03:55,737 --> 00:03:57,083
Please, Mama?

63
00:03:58,474 --> 00:04:00,921
Not that one.
That's just for Papa.

64
00:04:00,943 --> 00:04:04,725
You are clearly the commanding
officer in this family.

65
00:05:18,954 --> 00:05:20,500
'Night, little soldier.

66
00:05:20,522 --> 00:05:22,836
Good night, Mama.

67
00:05:31,333 --> 00:05:33,179
No need to panic.

68
00:05:33,200 --> 00:05:35,247
You'd be dead already
if I wanted it.

69
00:05:35,270 --> 00:05:37,618
What do you want?

70
00:05:38,172 --> 00:05:39,419
Your son.

71
00:06:28,290 --> 00:06:29,910
If you were looking
for a helpless victim,

72
00:06:29,925 --> 00:06:32,105
you came to the wrong house.

73
00:06:47,009 --> 00:06:49,289
You're out of practice Adeline.

74
00:06:51,546 --> 00:06:54,327
From what I've heard,
you were something to behold,

75
00:06:54,349 --> 00:06:56,763
before marriage and motherhood
made you soft.

76
00:06:58,854 --> 00:07:02,201
Leader of an elite squad within
the Green Berets called Team Seven.

77
00:07:02,223 --> 00:07:04,805
You trained Slade Wilson.

78
00:07:04,826 --> 00:07:07,441
Helped make him the killing
machine that he is today.

79
00:07:07,462 --> 00:07:10,276
"Killing machine"?

80
00:07:10,298 --> 00:07:12,345
He's a businessman.

81
00:07:12,367 --> 00:07:14,246
Oh, Adeline,

82
00:07:14,269 --> 00:07:16,248
there's so much you don't know.

83
00:07:16,271 --> 00:07:18,318
Who the hell are you?

84
00:07:18,874 --> 00:07:19,986
The Jackal.

85
00:07:37,359 --> 00:07:39,439
Molina sent you.

86
00:07:39,461 --> 00:07:42,282
<i>El Presidente</i> doesn't
like his generals plotting against him.

87
00:07:42,297 --> 00:07:44,678
He finds revolution distasteful.

88
00:07:44,700 --> 00:07:47,180
Then go ahead.
Cut my throat.

89
00:07:47,201 --> 00:07:49,649
You'll never
get out of here alive.

90
00:07:49,671 --> 00:07:51,017
Of course I will.

91
00:07:53,475 --> 00:07:54,888
What is this?

92
00:07:54,910 --> 00:07:56,363
The head of President Molina.

93
00:07:56,378 --> 00:07:58,592
Note the look of surprise
on his face.

94
00:07:58,613 --> 00:08:00,961
Very similar to
how you look right now.

95
00:08:04,152 --> 00:08:05,532
I don't understand.

96
00:08:05,554 --> 00:08:08,235
If Molina hired you
to assassinate me, then...

97
00:08:08,256 --> 00:08:10,269
I'm a mercenary,
not an idiot.

98
00:08:10,292 --> 00:08:12,539
Your president
was an oppressive fascist

99
00:08:12,561 --> 00:08:14,574
who ground his people
into the dirt.

100
00:08:14,596 --> 00:08:17,377
Under his rule,
San Miguel became a cesspool

101
00:08:17,399 --> 00:08:19,479
of poverty, hunger and disease,

102
00:08:19,501 --> 00:08:23,083
while he just grew richer
and fatter.

103
00:08:23,105 --> 00:08:24,751
Do better, General Suarez.

104
00:08:25,507 --> 00:08:26,853
Or this will be you.

105
00:08:28,443 --> 00:08:29,856
And, oh, yes,

106
00:08:29,878 --> 00:08:32,392
there is the little matter
of my fee.

107
00:08:41,590 --> 00:08:43,470
Which I am delighted to pay.

108
00:08:51,700 --> 00:08:53,780
<i>Took a few hits, I see.</i>

109
00:08:53,802 --> 00:08:55,615
It's nothing.

110
00:08:55,637 --> 00:08:57,958
<i>Do you ever consider what would
happen to Adeline and Joseph</i>

111
00:08:57,973 --> 00:09:00,954
<i>if you died on
one of these little jaunts?</i>

112
00:09:00,976 --> 00:09:03,957
<i>You've been doing this for
what, eight years now? Nine?</i>

113
00:09:03,979 --> 00:09:07,460
<i>Maybe it's time to stop being
a mercenary and start being...</i>

114
00:09:07,482 --> 00:09:09,830
I'll need transport
ASAP, Wintergreen.

115
00:09:09,851 --> 00:09:11,865
<i>And you will have it,
old friend.</i>

116
00:09:15,290 --> 00:09:18,538
<i>The older I get,
the more I envy your ability to heal.</i>

117
00:09:18,560 --> 00:09:21,374
<i>The Army certainly got
what they paid for.</i>

118
00:09:21,396 --> 00:09:22,843
And more.

119
00:09:37,679 --> 00:09:39,426
It's not working, dammit!

120
00:09:44,686 --> 00:09:47,234
- Will he live?
- Doesn't matter.

121
00:09:47,256 --> 00:09:48,702
We've failed again.

122
00:09:55,096 --> 00:09:56,543
They said...

123
00:09:56,565 --> 00:09:58,218
They said it was a miracle
I'm still alive.

124
00:09:58,233 --> 00:10:01,882
I told you not to volunteer
for that damn drug trial.

125
00:10:01,903 --> 00:10:04,057
When they wouldn't even tell you
what it was for, I knew that...

126
00:10:04,072 --> 00:10:05,552
It was my choice.

127
00:10:05,574 --> 00:10:06,953
I could have said no.

128
00:10:06,975 --> 00:10:08,421
Then why didn't you?

129
00:10:08,443 --> 00:10:10,324
Because they needed me.

130
00:10:10,345 --> 00:10:12,759
There were only a handful of
men that fit the profile...

131
00:10:12,781 --> 00:10:15,161
And you've always been
a good soldier.

132
00:10:16,051 --> 00:10:17,664
Maybe too good.

133
00:10:17,686 --> 00:10:19,699
They'll be sending me home
in a few days.

134
00:10:19,721 --> 00:10:21,268
And I'm going with you.

135
00:10:21,290 --> 00:10:22,736
But your duties...

136
00:10:22,757 --> 00:10:24,771
I've served my country.

137
00:10:24,793 --> 00:10:26,606
And done a damn good job of it.

138
00:10:26,628 --> 00:10:29,142
- But you need me now...
- No.

139
00:10:29,164 --> 00:10:30,877
You've got another 14 months.

140
00:10:30,899 --> 00:10:33,046
You do what you signed on to do.

141
00:10:35,271 --> 00:10:38,718
Let me try to build
a life for myself, for us.

142
00:10:39,207 --> 00:10:40,787
Then...

143
00:10:40,809 --> 00:10:42,323
Then, if you still want me...

144
00:10:42,345 --> 00:10:44,658
Why wouldn't I want you?

145
00:10:44,679 --> 00:10:46,294
I love you, Slade.

146
00:10:46,315 --> 00:10:47,994
We've got plans.

147
00:10:48,016 --> 00:10:49,696
A whole life ahead of us.

148
00:10:49,718 --> 00:10:52,599
The Army's the only life
I've ever known, Addie.

149
00:10:52,621 --> 00:10:55,802
Being that good soldier.
Following orders.

150
00:10:56,992 --> 00:10:58,738
Killing the enemy.

151
00:10:58,760 --> 00:11:00,974
There's more to you than that.

152
00:11:02,464 --> 00:11:03,743
I hope so.

153
00:14:04,112 --> 00:14:05,959
Addie?

154
00:14:22,465 --> 00:14:24,512
Dear God, what happened?

155
00:14:24,533 --> 00:14:25,979
Where's Joseph?

156
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:29,316
He said if I called the police,
he'd kill him.

157
00:14:29,938 --> 00:14:32,152
Who? Who did this?

158
00:14:32,874 --> 00:14:35,322
Said it's you he wants.

159
00:14:35,344 --> 00:14:36,390
Who did this?

160
00:14:37,513 --> 00:14:38,958
The Jackal.

161
00:14:38,980 --> 00:14:41,227
Who the hell is the Jackal?

162
00:14:41,250 --> 00:14:42,929
You know who he is!

163
00:14:42,951 --> 00:14:45,165
"I haven't lied to you since,"
you said,

164
00:14:45,186 --> 00:14:48,034
"and I will never
lie to you again."

165
00:14:48,056 --> 00:14:51,104
But it's all been
nothing but lies, hasn't it?

166
00:14:51,126 --> 00:14:52,513
I don't know
what you're talking about.

167
00:14:52,528 --> 00:14:54,073
Stop!

168
00:14:54,095 --> 00:14:56,976
The Jackal told me everything.

169
00:14:56,998 --> 00:14:59,979
The Army thought
the experiment was a failure,

170
00:15:00,001 --> 00:15:01,848
that their drug didn't work.

171
00:15:01,870 --> 00:15:04,017
That's why they discharged you.

172
00:15:04,038 --> 00:15:06,786
But it just took a little time
to turn you into...

173
00:15:06,808 --> 00:15:08,589
What did he call you?

174
00:15:08,611 --> 00:15:09,856
Deathstroke.

175
00:15:10,879 --> 00:15:12,959
I'm a businessman.

176
00:15:12,981 --> 00:15:15,728
That's what I always believed.

177
00:15:15,750 --> 00:15:18,898
Slade Wilson, a good
and decent man,

178
00:15:18,920 --> 00:15:20,800
who loved his wife and son,

179
00:15:20,822 --> 00:15:23,002
who'd do anything
for his family.

180
00:15:23,024 --> 00:15:25,372
But you're a goddamn mercenary.

181
00:15:25,394 --> 00:15:28,542
Selling death
to the highest bidder,

182
00:15:28,564 --> 00:15:30,377
and you hid it from me.

183
00:15:31,500 --> 00:15:32,912
All these years.

184
00:15:34,270 --> 00:15:35,300
Why?

185
00:15:39,874 --> 00:15:41,655
I'll bring Joseph back.

186
00:15:41,676 --> 00:15:44,958
And I'll bring the Jackal's
carcass back with me.

187
00:15:44,979 --> 00:15:48,061
I don't need you.
We don't need you.

188
00:15:48,082 --> 00:15:49,663
I can do this without you.

189
00:15:52,220 --> 00:15:53,833
Broken, damn it.

190
00:15:53,855 --> 00:15:55,768
In several places,
from the look of it.

191
00:15:56,124 --> 00:15:57,154
Go.

192
00:16:03,865 --> 00:16:06,012
When this is over, Addie,
we'll talk.

193
00:16:06,034 --> 00:16:08,047
Don't even try
to lie to me again,

194
00:16:08,069 --> 00:16:10,817
you manipulative son of a bitch.

195
00:16:10,838 --> 00:16:12,986
Just bring Joseph home.

196
00:16:13,007 --> 00:16:15,389
And God help you if you fail.

197
00:16:16,679 --> 00:16:18,091
I never fail.

198
00:16:38,833 --> 00:16:41,180
How's the wife,
Wilson?

199
00:16:41,202 --> 00:16:42,449
Show yourself.

200
00:16:48,277 --> 00:16:49,490
I'm right here.

201
00:16:50,878 --> 00:16:52,191
My son...

202
00:16:52,213 --> 00:16:55,061
Is fine.
Just a bargaining chip.

203
00:16:55,083 --> 00:16:57,897
Accept the bargain
and he doesn't get hurt.

204
00:16:57,919 --> 00:16:59,932
I won't work with H.I.V.E.

205
00:16:59,954 --> 00:17:02,101
So you said
the last time I asked.

206
00:17:02,123 --> 00:17:03,470
And I respect that.

207
00:17:03,492 --> 00:17:06,507
Unfortunately,
my superiors don't.

208
00:17:10,499 --> 00:17:13,781
They think your skills
would be of great value to us.

209
00:17:13,801 --> 00:17:15,148
You're terrorists.

210
00:17:15,169 --> 00:17:17,418
Equal opportunity murderers.

211
00:17:17,439 --> 00:17:19,886
Selling our services
to the highest bidder,

212
00:17:19,907 --> 00:17:21,322
just like you.

213
00:17:21,343 --> 00:17:23,923
Only difference is
you're small-time.

214
00:17:23,945 --> 00:17:26,025
H.I.V.E. thinks globally.

215
00:17:26,047 --> 00:17:27,368
How many innocent people,

216
00:17:27,383 --> 00:17:30,764
women and children
have died at your hands?

217
00:17:30,785 --> 00:17:33,467
Honestly,
I've lost count.

218
00:17:33,489 --> 00:17:37,738
But we're all murderers
under the skin, Wilson.

219
00:17:37,760 --> 00:17:39,740
It's just a matter of scale.

220
00:17:39,762 --> 00:17:43,444
Morality is delusion that fools
wear like a comforting cloak.

221
00:17:44,433 --> 00:17:46,913
But you're no fool.
Are you?

222
00:17:46,934 --> 00:17:49,717
A monster perhaps,
but not a fool.

223
00:17:49,738 --> 00:17:51,084
Monster?

224
00:17:51,105 --> 00:17:53,654
Yes, I kill for a living.

225
00:17:53,676 --> 00:17:55,689
But only if the cause is right.

226
00:17:55,711 --> 00:17:57,658
There are lines I won't cross.

227
00:17:57,680 --> 00:17:59,593
I don't know
if the widows and children

228
00:17:59,615 --> 00:18:03,062
of those soldiers you murdered
in San Miguel would agree.

229
00:18:03,719 --> 00:18:05,031
We're the same.

230
00:18:05,053 --> 00:18:06,500
Can't you see that?

231
00:18:06,522 --> 00:18:09,969
Men like us pretend
to have hearts and souls.

232
00:18:09,991 --> 00:18:11,204
But underneath that,

233
00:18:11,859 --> 00:18:13,072
only darkness.

234
00:18:15,897 --> 00:18:17,043
I...

235
00:18:20,569 --> 00:18:23,283
The answer is no.

236
00:18:24,673 --> 00:18:26,018
Reconsider.

237
00:18:57,972 --> 00:18:59,118
Enough!

238
00:19:03,010 --> 00:19:04,291
Enough.

239
00:19:29,738 --> 00:19:32,653
You do realize
that you've proven my point.

240
00:19:32,674 --> 00:19:36,122
She was
an extraordinary operative.

241
00:19:37,312 --> 00:19:39,526
But clearly
not extraordinary enough.

242
00:19:39,548 --> 00:19:42,729
Bronze Tiger's skills are legendary.

243
00:19:43,452 --> 00:19:44,665
And look at him.

244
00:19:47,054 --> 00:19:49,536
Give me my boy.

245
00:19:49,558 --> 00:19:52,104
Give me your answer.

246
00:19:52,126 --> 00:19:53,507
Will you join H.I.V.E.?

247
00:20:02,170 --> 00:20:04,618
Or will my man slit little
Joseph's throat here and now?

248
00:20:14,982 --> 00:20:17,397
Joseph, don't be afraid.

249
00:20:41,410 --> 00:20:42,440
Joe.

250
00:20:43,144 --> 00:20:44,324
Joseph!

251
00:20:45,614 --> 00:20:46,693
You're not gonna die.

252
00:20:46,715 --> 00:20:48,295
I swear to God
you're not gonna die.

253
00:21:41,135 --> 00:21:42,516
<i>Dear Joseph,</i>

254
00:21:46,207 --> 00:21:49,456
<i>your mother thinks it's best
that I stay away for a while.</i>

255
00:21:50,312 --> 00:21:51,525
<i>And I agree.</i>

256
00:22:02,524 --> 00:22:04,771
<i>You see, I have a secret,</i>

257
00:22:04,793 --> 00:22:08,041
<i>one I've never shared
with you before.</i>

258
00:22:08,062 --> 00:22:11,345
<i>I'm a knight, like the ones
in our favorite book,</i>

259
00:22:11,366 --> 00:22:13,513
<i>roaming a dangerous world.</i>

260
00:22:13,535 --> 00:22:16,683
<i>Righting wrongs,
slaying dragons.</i>

261
00:22:19,741 --> 00:22:23,657
<i>And I don't want those dragons
to hurt you, or your mom...</i>

262
00:22:24,613 --> 00:22:25,659
<i>ever again.</i>

263
00:23:13,095 --> 00:23:15,274
That was a mistake.

264
00:24:08,383 --> 00:24:09,930
Who sent you?

265
00:24:11,019 --> 00:24:12,049
Does it matter?

266
00:24:13,622 --> 00:24:14,935
I was paid a small fortune

267
00:24:14,956 --> 00:24:17,269
to liberate what's
hidden away downstairs.

268
00:24:18,126 --> 00:24:19,439
But frankly, Bora...

269
00:24:25,767 --> 00:24:28,515
...I would have done this one
for free.

270
00:25:01,069 --> 00:25:02,482
It's all right.

271
00:25:02,504 --> 00:25:05,385
No one's gonna hurt you
ever again.

272
00:26:08,570 --> 00:26:11,319
<i>Hello, Wilson.</i>

273
00:26:11,339 --> 00:26:13,987
<i>Or do you prefer "Deathstroke"?</i>

274
00:26:14,009 --> 00:26:15,039
Who the hell...

275
00:26:17,112 --> 00:26:19,593
<i>You can call me
the H.I.V.E. Queen.</i>

276
00:26:20,148 --> 00:26:21,394
H.I.V.E. is gone.

277
00:26:21,416 --> 00:26:23,331
I spent years
making sure of that.

278
00:26:23,351 --> 00:26:26,366
<i>No, not gone, underground.</i>

279
00:26:27,422 --> 00:26:29,202
<i>Regrouping.</i>

280
00:26:29,224 --> 00:26:32,505
<i>Dozens of independent cells
scattered across the world.</i>

281
00:26:32,527 --> 00:26:37,544
<i>And my little cell is very
interested in the Wilson family.</i>

282
00:26:37,566 --> 00:26:39,713
I turned H.I.V.E. down
ten years ago.

283
00:26:39,734 --> 00:26:41,681
- And if you think...
- <i>Don't flatter yourself.</i>

284
00:26:41,703 --> 00:26:44,384
<i>You made it clear then
that you were a bad fit.</i>

285
00:26:44,406 --> 00:26:47,988
<i>And really, why bother
with the father</i>

286
00:26:48,009 --> 00:26:50,056
<i>when I have the son?</i>

287
00:26:50,078 --> 00:26:51,108
What?

288
00:26:52,380 --> 00:26:53,793
Joseph?

289
00:26:53,815 --> 00:26:55,795
<i>You're a handgun, Slade.</i>

290
00:26:57,185 --> 00:27:00,667
<i>Your boy, he's a nuclear bomb.</i>

291
00:27:00,689 --> 00:27:03,304
<i>A bomb that belongs to me now.</i>

292
00:27:03,326 --> 00:27:04,871
What have you done to him?

293
00:27:08,063 --> 00:27:10,810
<i>Me? Don't you know?</i>

294
00:27:11,433 --> 00:27:13,013
<i>You did this.</i>

295
00:27:15,437 --> 00:27:17,050
<i>You didn't know.</i>

296
00:27:18,307 --> 00:27:19,819
<i>More's the pity.</i>

297
00:27:51,106 --> 00:27:54,355
I chose that school in
Switzerland for the security.

298
00:27:54,377 --> 00:27:55,789
You chose poorly.

299
00:27:57,479 --> 00:27:59,327
Did you know?

300
00:27:59,348 --> 00:28:01,768
That whatever the Army did to
alter your biology, your genetics,

301
00:28:01,783 --> 00:28:03,263
was passed on to Joseph?

302
00:28:03,286 --> 00:28:04,432
Of course not.

303
00:28:04,452 --> 00:28:05,999
From what
that H.I.V.E. Queen said,

304
00:28:06,021 --> 00:28:08,034
his abilities are
very different than mine.

305
00:28:08,056 --> 00:28:10,570
Not physical in nature,
psychic.

306
00:28:11,459 --> 00:28:12,839
What?

307
00:28:12,861 --> 00:28:14,541
There were times when I'd...

308
00:28:16,031 --> 00:28:17,510
feel him.

309
00:28:17,532 --> 00:28:19,045
As if he was
in the room with me.

310
00:28:19,067 --> 00:28:21,748
But I thought
I was just imagining it.

311
00:28:21,770 --> 00:28:23,083
He should have been with you.

312
00:28:23,104 --> 00:28:24,624
How could you just
send him away like that?

313
00:28:24,639 --> 00:28:26,786
I did it to keep him safe.

314
00:28:26,808 --> 00:28:28,422
I could have kept him safe.

315
00:28:28,443 --> 00:28:29,990
The way you did last time?

316
00:28:30,011 --> 00:28:32,892
When that animal cut his
throat and left him mute?

317
00:28:32,914 --> 00:28:35,396
You punished me enough
for it, didn't you?

318
00:28:35,418 --> 00:28:36,896
Locked me out of his life.

319
00:28:39,587 --> 00:28:41,501
And you never
once questioned it.

320
00:28:41,523 --> 00:28:43,069
Never once tried to see him.

321
00:28:43,091 --> 00:28:45,605
Another man would have
fought me tooth and nail,

322
00:28:45,627 --> 00:28:47,674
would have begged
to see his son.

323
00:28:47,696 --> 00:28:50,243
But you? One pathetic letter,

324
00:28:50,266 --> 00:28:52,545
and then you were gone forever.

325
00:28:52,567 --> 00:28:53,947
Why?

326
00:28:53,969 --> 00:28:56,750
I always seem to be
asking you that. Why?

327
00:28:56,771 --> 00:28:58,386
The past is dead, Addie,

328
00:28:58,407 --> 00:29:00,820
and nothing we do,
nothing we say, can change it.

329
00:29:00,842 --> 00:29:02,956
But the past isn't dead, Slade.

330
00:29:02,978 --> 00:29:05,825
It's happening all over again.

331
00:29:05,847 --> 00:29:07,428
So what are we
going to do about it?

332
00:29:07,450 --> 00:29:08,762
"We"?

333
00:29:08,783 --> 00:29:11,064
You're not going after him
alone this time.

334
00:29:11,086 --> 00:29:12,932
I'm going with you.

335
00:29:12,954 --> 00:29:15,001
Do you remember
what the Jackal did to you?

336
00:29:15,023 --> 00:29:16,069
Oh, I remember.

337
00:29:16,091 --> 00:29:19,139
He broke me.
Humiliated me.

338
00:29:19,160 --> 00:29:20,874
And it was my own fault.

339
00:29:20,895 --> 00:29:23,411
I put so much energy
into being a mother,

340
00:29:23,432 --> 00:29:24,778
being your wife,

341
00:29:24,799 --> 00:29:26,646
that I lost my center.

342
00:29:26,668 --> 00:29:28,148
Well, I've found it again.

343
00:29:30,038 --> 00:29:32,018
You haven't been
on a combat mission in years.

344
00:29:38,414 --> 00:29:40,560
Guess I'm just too rusty, huh?

345
00:29:44,253 --> 00:29:46,199
Stay out of it, Adeline.

346
00:29:46,221 --> 00:29:47,834
Slade. Slade.

347
00:29:53,262 --> 00:29:54,292
Good luck.

348
00:31:16,878 --> 00:31:19,259
It's a beautiful home,
Colonel Kapoor,

349
00:31:26,654 --> 00:31:29,202
Built with H.I.V.E. money,
as I recall.

350
00:31:29,224 --> 00:31:34,140
I stopped working for them years
ago, as you no doubt also recall.

351
00:31:34,896 --> 00:31:36,676
You had no choice.

352
00:31:36,698 --> 00:31:38,011
I destroyed them.

353
00:31:38,601 --> 00:31:40,213
Or so I thought.

354
00:31:40,235 --> 00:31:42,081
They're back?

355
00:31:42,103 --> 00:31:44,391
<i>And I want information
about one cell in particular,</i>

356
00:31:44,406 --> 00:31:47,020
<i>led by a woman who calls
herself the H.I.V.E. Queen.</i>

357
00:31:47,041 --> 00:31:49,923
<i>I closed the door
on that chapter of my life.</i>

358
00:31:49,944 --> 00:31:52,660
<i>I've spoken to
close to a dozen former operatives</i>

359
00:31:52,680 --> 00:31:54,428
<i>who all claim the same thing.</i>

360
00:31:55,049 --> 00:31:56,069
And?

361
00:31:56,084 --> 00:31:57,897
Telling the truth,
as far as I know.

362
00:31:58,254 --> 00:31:59,500
And?

363
00:31:59,522 --> 00:32:01,468
Don't worry, Colonel,
I left them all intact.

364
00:32:01,490 --> 00:32:03,470
Aside from Myshkin.

365
00:32:03,492 --> 00:32:06,340
He was so afraid to even talk about
H.I.V.E. that he killed himself.

366
00:32:06,362 --> 00:32:09,275
I was never in very deep,
Deathstroke, you know that.

367
00:32:09,298 --> 00:32:12,712
As a colonel I could
provide a favor here and there.

368
00:32:12,734 --> 00:32:14,682
For which you were
richly rewarded.

369
00:32:14,702 --> 00:32:18,419
And the truth is,
I was relieved when you took them down.

370
00:32:19,508 --> 00:32:22,423
I have a wife now. A family.

371
00:32:22,444 --> 00:32:25,659
A little graft is one thing, but
getting involved with H.I.V.E. again...

372
00:32:25,680 --> 00:32:26,793
No.

373
00:32:31,353 --> 00:32:33,467
If you hear anything,

374
00:32:33,489 --> 00:32:35,703
you contact me immediately.

375
00:32:35,757 --> 00:32:36,903
I will.

376
00:33:01,317 --> 00:33:03,263
<i>This better be good, Kapoor.</i>

377
00:33:46,462 --> 00:33:47,492
Impressive.

378
00:33:48,564 --> 00:33:50,176
This is a surprise.

379
00:33:58,139 --> 00:33:59,586
Look at you.

380
00:33:59,608 --> 00:34:02,221
Hero of the Kaznian revolution.

381
00:34:02,977 --> 00:34:04,692
You know how it goes.

382
00:34:04,713 --> 00:34:06,993
Southern Kaznians
take the capital.

383
00:34:07,015 --> 00:34:09,563
A few years go by,
and then the north takes it.

384
00:34:09,585 --> 00:34:11,230
Been going on for years.

385
00:34:11,253 --> 00:34:14,067
I've worked for both sides.
They're very generous.

386
00:34:14,088 --> 00:34:17,270
And children starve.
Innocents die.

387
00:34:17,293 --> 00:34:20,173
Still singing the same song,
huh, Wilson?

388
00:34:20,194 --> 00:34:22,275
The mercenary with a conscience.

389
00:34:22,298 --> 00:34:23,976
The rest of us...

390
00:34:23,998 --> 00:34:25,412
we're beneath you!

391
00:34:30,872 --> 00:34:33,920
I didn't come here
to debate, Tiger.

392
00:34:33,941 --> 00:34:36,022
Or to fight.

393
00:34:36,044 --> 00:34:38,858
I came here for information.

394
00:34:38,880 --> 00:34:40,860
If it's dope on H.I.V.E.
you want...

395
00:34:53,227 --> 00:34:55,007
You have nothing
to do with them.

396
00:34:55,029 --> 00:34:56,909
Didn't even know
they still existed.

397
00:35:04,972 --> 00:35:06,919
Oh, I knew.

398
00:35:06,941 --> 00:35:08,655
Once the Jackal took over.

399
00:35:10,679 --> 00:35:12,493
Jackal? He's alive?

400
00:35:15,917 --> 00:35:18,131
You should've made sure
he was dead.

401
00:35:20,589 --> 00:35:24,036
That man has
a serious hate on for you.

402
00:35:27,796 --> 00:35:29,710
After that mess with your kid,

403
00:35:29,732 --> 00:35:32,912
Jackal decided that H.I.V.E.
needed reorganization.

404
00:35:32,934 --> 00:35:36,015
New leadership.
So he stepped back.

405
00:35:36,037 --> 00:35:39,118
And let
me wipe out his competition.

406
00:35:43,945 --> 00:35:47,594
And then, very quietly,
put the pieces back together.

407
00:36:09,304 --> 00:36:11,518
But I was tired
of taking orders.

408
00:36:11,540 --> 00:36:12,985
Decided to freelance.

409
00:36:14,942 --> 00:36:16,690
Worked out pretty well.

410
00:36:30,859 --> 00:36:32,205
Again?

411
00:36:32,226 --> 00:36:33,874
Son of a bitch.

412
00:36:33,896 --> 00:36:35,909
You did it again.

413
00:36:35,930 --> 00:36:38,345
Where can I find
the H.I.V.E Queen?

414
00:36:52,947 --> 00:36:54,260
Fine.

415
00:36:54,283 --> 00:36:55,995
The Kerguelen Islands.

416
00:36:56,885 --> 00:36:58,097
Thank you.

417
00:36:59,888 --> 00:37:01,267
That's my ride.

418
00:37:13,769 --> 00:37:15,081
Don't bother.

419
00:37:15,102 --> 00:37:17,751
Where he's headed,
there's no coming back.

420
00:37:21,075 --> 00:37:22,356
Oh, shit.

421
00:37:34,623 --> 00:37:38,271
So, how the hell did you get your
hands on an aircraft like this?

422
00:37:38,293 --> 00:37:39,773
Somebody owed me a favor.

423
00:37:39,795 --> 00:37:41,642
A very big one, apparently.

424
00:37:43,231 --> 00:37:44,984
There's every chance
they know you're coming.

425
00:37:44,999 --> 00:37:46,245
I'm counting on it.

426
00:37:46,268 --> 00:37:48,047
You'll never change.

427
00:37:48,069 --> 00:37:49,917
Having second thoughts,
Wintergreen?

428
00:37:49,938 --> 00:37:51,117
On the contrary.

429
00:37:51,138 --> 00:37:53,219
Since MI6 retired me,

430
00:37:53,242 --> 00:37:57,691
the only fun I ever have is when you
invite me along on these little jaunts.

431
00:37:57,713 --> 00:37:59,526
I'll be too old for this
soon enough.

432
00:37:59,548 --> 00:38:02,396
Well, I'm probably
too old for it now,

433
00:38:02,417 --> 00:38:04,698
but I'm not ready
for the nursing home just yet.

434
00:38:04,720 --> 00:38:06,300
This one's no jaunt.

435
00:38:06,321 --> 00:38:08,035
Joseph's life is at stake.

436
00:38:08,055 --> 00:38:09,636
And what kind of
godfather would I be

437
00:38:09,658 --> 00:38:11,972
if I wasn't helping you
bring him home?

438
00:38:11,994 --> 00:38:13,407
In fact, I...

439
00:38:14,028 --> 00:38:15,976
There they are.

440
00:38:15,998 --> 00:38:20,514
The Kerguelens. Also known as
the Desolation Islands.

441
00:38:21,202 --> 00:38:22,683
Aptly named, I think.

442
00:38:30,579 --> 00:38:32,292
<i>Best of luck, Slade.</i>

443
00:38:32,314 --> 00:38:34,394
I don't believe in luck.

444
00:38:34,416 --> 00:38:36,797
But in this case, I'll take it.

445
00:39:56,197 --> 00:39:57,944
I was expecting an army.

446
00:39:59,133 --> 00:40:00,747
They don't need an army.

447
00:40:02,070 --> 00:40:03,817
They've got me.

448
00:40:03,839 --> 00:40:07,621
Sandra Wu San.
Also known as Lady Shiva.

449
00:40:07,643 --> 00:40:09,489
There are people
who consider you

450
00:40:09,511 --> 00:40:12,292
the deadliest hand-to-hand
combatant in the world.

451
00:40:12,314 --> 00:40:13,860
And they would be right.

452
00:40:19,855 --> 00:40:21,334
What are you doing?

453
00:40:21,356 --> 00:40:22,703
Surrendering.

454
00:40:22,724 --> 00:40:25,204
I do not accept your surrender.

455
00:40:25,226 --> 00:40:26,773
<i>Not tonight, Shiva.</i>

456
00:40:26,795 --> 00:40:28,075
<i>I want him alive.</i>

457
00:40:28,096 --> 00:40:29,342
<i>Bring him to me.</i>

458
00:40:30,799 --> 00:40:32,412
Yes, my Queen.

459
00:40:32,968 --> 00:40:33,998
Up.

460
00:40:52,186 --> 00:40:54,868
Surrender is a clever strategy.

461
00:40:54,890 --> 00:40:57,971
Easier than fighting
your way into the fortress.

462
00:40:57,993 --> 00:41:00,540
But it won't be
quite as easy getting out.

463
00:41:03,197 --> 00:41:04,444
What?

464
00:41:04,466 --> 00:41:06,012
You're just a child.

465
00:41:14,543 --> 00:41:17,691
And you're a dinosaur
whose time has passed.

466
00:41:22,384 --> 00:41:24,331
Let's cut the bullshit,
shall we?

467
00:41:24,352 --> 00:41:26,900
Where's my boy? Where's Joseph.

468
00:41:27,723 --> 00:41:30,504
Yes. Let's cut the bullshit.

469
00:41:34,796 --> 00:41:36,176
Where is he?

470
00:41:36,198 --> 00:41:37,778
Such concern.

471
00:41:37,799 --> 00:41:41,381
And yet, you abandoned Joseph
without a second thought

472
00:41:41,403 --> 00:41:43,150
just as his mother did.

473
00:41:43,171 --> 00:41:47,320
Left him trapped, isolated,
friendless in that school.

474
00:41:47,342 --> 00:41:50,857
His mind, his very soul,
on fire.

475
00:41:50,879 --> 00:41:52,359
I didn't know.

476
00:41:52,380 --> 00:41:53,560
Could it be...

477
00:41:55,350 --> 00:41:56,863
you didn't want to?

478
00:41:58,720 --> 00:42:02,202
So, he's what,
your little lab rat?

479
00:42:02,224 --> 00:42:04,037
We're going to train him.

480
00:42:04,059 --> 00:42:06,473
Help him master his powers.

481
00:42:06,495 --> 00:42:08,675
You've got him
locked in a damn cage.

482
00:42:08,697 --> 00:42:10,477
For his own protection.

483
00:42:10,499 --> 00:42:14,314
His psychic energies
are still wildly unstable.

484
00:42:14,336 --> 00:42:15,682
But his potential,

485
00:42:16,171 --> 00:42:17,350
limitless.

486
00:42:17,372 --> 00:42:20,053
- As a weapon.
- Yes.

487
00:42:20,742 --> 00:42:22,222
Think of it.

488
00:42:22,245 --> 00:42:25,759
Manipulation on a global scale
through the power of the mind.

489
00:42:25,781 --> 00:42:28,628
Domination of the planet
with no bullets.

490
00:42:28,650 --> 00:42:29,763
No bombs.

491
00:42:29,785 --> 00:42:33,466
What country on Earth
could resist us?

492
00:42:37,492 --> 00:42:38,972
Joseph? Joseph!

493
00:42:40,328 --> 00:42:41,474
Joseph!

494
00:42:41,496 --> 00:42:42,609
Don't be afraid.

495
00:42:46,701 --> 00:42:47,731
Joe...

496
00:42:49,971 --> 00:42:52,786
"Joseph" was the name
you gave him.

497
00:42:53,608 --> 00:42:55,388
But I've given him a new name.

498
00:42:55,410 --> 00:42:56,823
A better name.

499
00:42:57,280 --> 00:42:58,625
Jericho.

500
00:42:58,647 --> 00:43:00,360
Because, with my help,

501
00:43:00,382 --> 00:43:04,731
he's going to bring the walls
of the old order tumbling down.

502
00:43:09,391 --> 00:43:10,971
Be honest, Wilson.

503
00:43:10,992 --> 00:43:12,939
You don't really care about him.

504
00:43:13,461 --> 00:43:14,741
You never did.

505
00:43:14,763 --> 00:43:16,910
This is just another
adventure to you.

506
00:43:16,932 --> 00:43:20,146
Another chance to prove
your questionable manhood.

507
00:43:20,735 --> 00:43:21,765
But here,

508
00:43:22,571 --> 00:43:25,652
he'll find a home, a family.

509
00:43:29,144 --> 00:43:31,124
<i>Help me, Papa.</i>

510
00:43:31,146 --> 00:43:32,893
<i>Get me out of here!</i>

511
00:43:32,914 --> 00:43:33,944
<i>Please!</i>

512
00:43:35,150 --> 00:43:36,463
Get back, buddy.

513
00:43:40,188 --> 00:43:41,501
No!

514
00:44:39,214 --> 00:44:41,295
<i>I can help.
Put me down.</i>

515
00:44:41,317 --> 00:44:43,096
- You're weak.
- <i>I'm all right.</i>

516
00:44:49,858 --> 00:44:50,888
Joe.

517
00:44:52,427 --> 00:44:53,840
<i>I know a way out.</i>

518
00:44:56,731 --> 00:44:58,346
<i>This will get us to the surface.</i>

519
00:44:58,367 --> 00:45:00,314
<i>But I don't know what to do
once we're up there.</i>

520
00:45:00,336 --> 00:45:01,681
I've got that covered.

521
00:45:01,703 --> 00:45:03,516
Wintergreen, it's time.

522
00:45:03,538 --> 00:45:04,951
<i>On my way, Slade.</i>

523
00:45:13,848 --> 00:45:15,228
<i>That's all...</i>

524
00:45:15,251 --> 00:45:16,596
<i>That's all I can...</i>

525
00:45:18,653 --> 00:45:20,100
Wintergreen.

526
00:45:20,121 --> 00:45:22,635
Wintergreen?

527
00:45:22,657 --> 00:45:24,804
<i>Uncle William's not coming.</i>

528
00:45:24,826 --> 00:45:26,239
What?

529
00:45:26,262 --> 00:45:27,907
<i>I blocked the signal.</i>

530
00:45:27,929 --> 00:45:28,949
But I heard him.

531
00:45:28,964 --> 00:45:31,177
You heard
what I wanted you to hear.

532
00:45:31,933 --> 00:45:33,780
Joseph, why?

533
00:45:33,802 --> 00:45:36,850
Did you really think
I would betray my own sister?

534
00:45:37,406 --> 00:45:38,518
Sister?

535
00:45:46,715 --> 00:45:49,497
The H.I.V.E. Queen, she's...

536
00:45:49,517 --> 00:45:50,630
<i>Your daughter.</i>

537
00:45:52,654 --> 00:45:54,667
You really didn't know?

538
00:45:54,689 --> 00:45:56,803
Joseph, listen to me.
I came here...

539
00:45:56,825 --> 00:45:59,973
<i>Ride to the rescue
like a knight in shining armor?</i>

540
00:46:02,063 --> 00:46:03,777
Joseph. Joseph!

541
00:46:04,400 --> 00:46:05,712
<i>My name</i>

542
00:46:06,268 --> 00:46:07,314
<i>is Jericho!</i>

543
00:46:11,374 --> 00:46:13,186
<i>Joseph's gone.</i>

544
00:46:13,208 --> 00:46:14,238
Joseph!

545
00:46:19,948 --> 00:46:22,695
<i>Good-bye, Deathstroke.</i>

546
00:46:46,641 --> 00:46:49,222
Joseph.

547
00:47:00,289 --> 00:47:02,669
Well done, boy. Well done.

548
00:47:18,274 --> 00:47:19,320
<i>Dark.</i>

549
00:47:21,109 --> 00:47:22,188
<i>Stillness.</i>

550
00:47:23,446 --> 00:47:24,476
<i>Peace.</i>

551
00:47:25,514 --> 00:47:26,659
<i>Oblivion.</i>

552
00:47:29,084 --> 00:47:32,966
<i>Is it such a terrible thing
to embrace the void,</i>

553
00:47:34,356 --> 00:47:36,303
<i>surrender to the silence,</i>

554
00:47:37,293 --> 00:47:38,323
<i>die?</i>

555
00:47:40,829 --> 00:47:42,909
<i>But I can't die now.</i>

556
00:47:42,931 --> 00:47:45,211
<i>One day, maybe soon.</i>

557
00:47:46,134 --> 00:47:47,947
<i>But not yet.</i>

558
00:47:49,771 --> 00:47:52,185
<i>Joseph needs me.</i>

559
00:47:52,207 --> 00:47:53,320
<i>My son needs me.</i>

560
00:47:54,642 --> 00:47:55,755
<i>And I...</i>

561
00:47:57,011 --> 00:47:58,041
<i>have...</i>

562
00:47:58,713 --> 00:48:00,226
<i>to live!</i>

563
00:48:06,621 --> 00:48:08,435
Easy. Easy.

564
00:48:08,457 --> 00:48:11,070
How am I even alive?

565
00:48:11,893 --> 00:48:13,641
You almost weren't.

566
00:48:13,661 --> 00:48:16,075
If I hadn't
fished you out in time...

567
00:48:16,097 --> 00:48:17,611
Addie?

568
00:48:17,632 --> 00:48:21,448
You may have an incredible
ability to heal, Slade.

569
00:48:21,470 --> 00:48:23,016
But you're not immortal.

570
00:48:27,942 --> 00:48:30,723
And one of these days,
you won't be coming back.

571
00:48:34,350 --> 00:48:37,063
Told you I wasn't gonna
let you do this alone.

572
00:48:37,785 --> 00:48:39,300
Where are we?

573
00:48:39,321 --> 00:48:40,434
On a boat.

574
00:48:40,456 --> 00:48:43,370
Far enough away
from that damn island.

575
00:48:43,392 --> 00:48:44,837
How did...

576
00:48:44,859 --> 00:48:46,239
How did you find me?

577
00:48:46,262 --> 00:48:48,475
I've been on you the whole time.

578
00:48:48,497 --> 00:48:51,345
Used a nano-tracker that I
procured from an old friend.

579
00:48:51,367 --> 00:48:54,847
Tiny GPS device that lodged
into your intestinal tract.

580
00:48:55,970 --> 00:48:58,851
- But how did...
- Sealed with a kiss.

581
00:49:04,712 --> 00:49:07,227
You implanted it
with your tongue?

582
00:49:09,251 --> 00:49:11,931
And here I thought
I'd won your heart again.

583
00:49:11,953 --> 00:49:13,434
It's got a limited shelf life.

584
00:49:13,455 --> 00:49:15,735
Should dissolve
in another few days.

585
00:49:16,325 --> 00:49:17,870
Drink this.

586
00:49:17,892 --> 00:49:21,207
A mix of herbs that should help
speed up your natural healing.

587
00:49:21,229 --> 00:49:22,215
Ugh.

588
00:49:22,230 --> 00:49:24,010
Drink it, tough guy.

589
00:49:29,771 --> 00:49:30,917
Ah...

590
00:49:31,373 --> 00:49:32,686
Wait.

591
00:49:32,707 --> 00:49:35,154
You said you got your tracker
from an old friend.

592
00:49:36,177 --> 00:49:37,924
Wintergreen.

593
00:49:37,946 --> 00:49:39,460
You two have been conspiring?

594
00:49:39,481 --> 00:49:40,793
Not conspiring,

595
00:49:40,815 --> 00:49:44,465
just sharing information
and resources.

596
00:49:44,486 --> 00:49:45,999
When I see that old man...

597
00:49:46,020 --> 00:49:49,002
If you're going to be angry
at someone, try yourself.

598
00:49:49,023 --> 00:49:51,938
You've made some terrible
choices in your life, Slade.

599
00:49:51,960 --> 00:49:53,741
And the people you love,

600
00:49:53,761 --> 00:49:55,942
that you claim to love,

601
00:49:55,964 --> 00:49:57,977
have paid a terrible price.

602
00:50:03,539 --> 00:50:05,352
So he's dead?

603
00:50:05,374 --> 00:50:08,054
The sharks have made
a meal of him by now.

604
00:50:08,076 --> 00:50:11,057
You must feel a profound sense
of satisfaction, Rose.

605
00:50:11,647 --> 00:50:13,494
I wish I did.

606
00:50:13,515 --> 00:50:17,196
I've wanted this for so long,
but now that I have it...

607
00:50:17,218 --> 00:50:20,334
Let it go, child.
You've done well.

608
00:50:20,356 --> 00:50:21,635
Made me proud.

609
00:50:21,657 --> 00:50:23,570
Now let's move on
with our plans.

610
00:50:24,460 --> 00:50:26,005
We need more time.

611
00:50:26,027 --> 00:50:27,474
Jericho is not ready.

612
00:50:27,496 --> 00:50:30,577
You'll make sure he's ready,
won't you?

613
00:50:30,599 --> 00:50:32,313
- But...
- Won't you?

614
00:50:33,234 --> 00:50:34,481
Yes.

615
00:50:34,503 --> 00:50:35,882
I have faith in you, Rose.

616
00:50:35,903 --> 00:50:38,117
I've always had faith in you.

617
00:50:38,139 --> 00:50:40,119
Since the day we met

618
00:50:40,141 --> 00:50:43,791
and I rescued you
from a hellish existence.

619
00:50:43,811 --> 00:50:45,825
It wasn't all hell.

620
00:50:47,683 --> 00:50:48,861
<i>My mother,</i>

621
00:50:48,883 --> 00:50:50,597
<i>she loved me.</i>

622
00:50:50,619 --> 00:50:52,766
<i>Yes, she did.</i>

623
00:50:52,787 --> 00:50:54,702
<i>After Wilson abandoned her.</i>

624
00:50:54,723 --> 00:50:56,470
<i>Left her pregnant and alone,</i>

625
00:50:56,492 --> 00:50:59,906
<i>she sacrificed everything
to build a good life for you.</i>

626
00:51:05,467 --> 00:51:07,348
<i>And perhaps,
it would have been good...</i>

627
00:51:10,972 --> 00:51:12,386
<i>...had she lived.</i>

628
00:51:15,910 --> 00:51:17,558
<i>And you were left alone.</i>

629
00:51:18,714 --> 00:51:20,394
<i>And Wilson,</i>

630
00:51:20,416 --> 00:51:22,895
<i>did he ever look back
and wonder?</i>

631
00:51:22,917 --> 00:51:24,431
<i>If he'd bothered,</i>

632
00:51:24,453 --> 00:51:26,933
<i>he might have discovered
that he had a daughter</i>

633
00:51:26,954 --> 00:51:29,202
<i>living on the streets
of Phnom Penh.</i>

634
00:51:31,527 --> 00:51:34,508
<i>But your father
did leave you one legacy.</i>

635
00:51:34,530 --> 00:51:37,378
<i>He passed his altered genetics
on to you.</i>

636
00:51:39,501 --> 00:51:40,814
<i>Speed,</i>

637
00:51:40,835 --> 00:51:42,081
<i>stamina,</i>

638
00:51:42,970 --> 00:51:44,117
<i>heightened strength...</i>

639
00:51:46,140 --> 00:51:47,321
<i>What a gift.</i>

640
00:51:48,243 --> 00:51:50,022
<i>It was a curse.</i>

641
00:51:55,250 --> 00:51:57,297
<i>I suppose it was at first.</i>

642
00:51:59,722 --> 00:52:00,752
<i>But then...</i>

643
00:52:03,625 --> 00:52:05,104
<i>I found you.</i>

644
00:52:06,462 --> 00:52:09,041
Took you under my wing,
trained you,

645
00:52:09,063 --> 00:52:10,943
became the father you never had.

646
00:52:10,965 --> 00:52:13,279
Made you a queen.

647
00:52:13,302 --> 00:52:16,015
And now, you'll make
your brother a king.

648
00:52:16,037 --> 00:52:17,083
And together...

649
00:52:17,105 --> 00:52:19,118
We'll rule the world?

650
00:52:19,140 --> 00:52:22,088
No. We'll rule the rulers.

651
00:52:22,110 --> 00:52:24,223
So much better that way.

652
00:52:24,246 --> 00:52:26,894
Project Jericho launches
in ten days, Rose.

653
00:52:26,914 --> 00:52:30,431
I have my final preparations
to see to and you have yours.

654
00:52:30,918 --> 00:52:32,064
Be ready.

655
00:52:32,920 --> 00:52:34,735
Will I see you then?

656
00:52:34,757 --> 00:52:36,637
It's been more than a year.

657
00:52:36,658 --> 00:52:38,772
You know I have to
remain in seclusion.

658
00:52:38,794 --> 00:52:40,940
No one can know
where the H.I.V.E. Lord is.

659
00:52:40,962 --> 00:52:42,443
Not even you.

660
00:52:42,464 --> 00:52:44,177
But this, child,

661
00:52:44,198 --> 00:52:46,179
I wouldn't miss for the world.

662
00:52:52,541 --> 00:52:53,571
<i>You okay?</i>

663
00:52:56,879 --> 00:52:58,224
I am now.

664
00:53:03,752 --> 00:53:05,998
I didn't know
Lillian was pregnant.

665
00:53:06,020 --> 00:53:07,701
She never told me.

666
00:53:07,723 --> 00:53:10,042
- If I had known...
- You would've been the father to that girl

667
00:53:10,057 --> 00:53:11,572
that you were to Joseph?

668
00:53:12,761 --> 00:53:15,442
Years ago, when you told me
about Lillian,

669
00:53:15,464 --> 00:53:17,744
you said she didn't mean
anything to you.

670
00:53:19,200 --> 00:53:20,347
Was that true?

671
00:53:20,836 --> 00:53:22,048
She didn't.

672
00:53:22,069 --> 00:53:23,750
Not like you, Addie.

673
00:53:23,772 --> 00:53:25,084
But?

674
00:53:25,106 --> 00:53:28,054
After I realized
what had happened to me...

675
00:53:28,075 --> 00:53:30,424
what the army
had turned me into, I felt...

676
00:53:30,846 --> 00:53:31,876
lost.

677
00:53:32,481 --> 00:53:33,594
Untethered.

678
00:53:33,615 --> 00:53:35,796
I needed time
to sort through things.

679
00:53:35,818 --> 00:53:38,130
So, I travelled. Looking for...

680
00:53:38,152 --> 00:53:40,132
Something I couldn't give you?

681
00:53:40,154 --> 00:53:41,535
I don't know.

682
00:53:41,557 --> 00:53:44,003
Maybe it was easier
turning to a stranger.

683
00:53:44,025 --> 00:53:45,973
Lillian was a good woman.

684
00:53:45,993 --> 00:53:47,774
Sweet. Kind.

685
00:53:47,796 --> 00:53:49,309
So you did care about her.

686
00:53:49,331 --> 00:53:50,577
Yes. But not like...

687
00:53:50,599 --> 00:53:53,179
And just left her,
pregnant and alone.

688
00:53:53,201 --> 00:53:55,382
I didn't know about the child.

689
00:53:55,404 --> 00:53:57,284
Would you rather I'd stayed
with her and not...

690
00:53:57,306 --> 00:53:59,218
I'd rather
it had never happened.

691
00:53:59,241 --> 00:54:01,020
It sounds funny, I know.

692
00:54:01,042 --> 00:54:02,556
But my affair with Lillian,

693
00:54:02,578 --> 00:54:05,792
it's what made me realize
that you were the only one.

694
00:54:05,814 --> 00:54:06,834
That no other woman could...

695
00:54:06,849 --> 00:54:08,295
I'm not laughing.

696
00:54:08,317 --> 00:54:09,963
I didn't mean it like that.

697
00:54:09,984 --> 00:54:11,498
What did you mean?

698
00:54:11,520 --> 00:54:12,766
Addie, I...

699
00:54:19,428 --> 00:54:22,275
Doesn't matter now, does it?

700
00:54:22,731 --> 00:54:23,977
No.

701
00:54:23,998 --> 00:54:25,445
Not when you
destroyed our family,

702
00:54:25,467 --> 00:54:27,648
and another one
you didn't even know you had.

703
00:54:27,669 --> 00:54:30,182
That's your forte, isn't it?
Destruction.

704
00:54:30,204 --> 00:54:32,953
If you feel that way,
then why the hell are you helping me?

705
00:54:32,975 --> 00:54:34,688
I'm not helping you.

706
00:54:34,710 --> 00:54:36,055
I'm helping Joseph.

707
00:54:36,077 --> 00:54:37,658
And once this is done,

708
00:54:38,145 --> 00:54:39,393
so are we.

709
00:54:45,521 --> 00:54:48,234
<i>We did
the right thing, didn't we?</i>

710
00:54:48,924 --> 00:54:49,943
Yes.

711
00:54:49,958 --> 00:54:51,838
Of course, we did.

712
00:54:51,860 --> 00:54:53,840
He was a monster.

713
00:54:53,862 --> 00:54:55,876
He had to die.

714
00:54:55,898 --> 00:54:57,611
<i>He was a knight once.</i>

715
00:54:57,633 --> 00:54:58,912
What?

716
00:54:58,934 --> 00:55:00,179
<i>Nothing.</i>

717
00:55:01,670 --> 00:55:04,451
I know a part of you
still loves them.

718
00:55:05,039 --> 00:55:06,820
You can't help it.

719
00:55:06,842 --> 00:55:11,090
But Slade Wilson
never gave a damn about you.

720
00:55:11,112 --> 00:55:13,225
His entire life was a lie.

721
00:55:13,749 --> 00:55:15,227
And your mother,

722
00:55:15,250 --> 00:55:17,030
if she really loved you,

723
00:55:17,051 --> 00:55:20,232
would she have locked
you away in that school,

724
00:55:20,255 --> 00:55:21,835
left you there to rot?

725
00:55:23,492 --> 00:55:24,972
Would she?

726
00:55:24,993 --> 00:55:26,172
<i>No.</i>

727
00:55:40,943 --> 00:55:43,523
We were both so alone, Jericho.

728
00:55:43,545 --> 00:55:45,257
So alone.

729
00:55:45,280 --> 00:55:48,428
But we found each other,
didn't we?

730
00:55:50,819 --> 00:55:54,200
I guess we can thank
Deathstroke for that much.

731
00:55:54,221 --> 00:55:56,268
Years before we ever met,

732
00:55:56,291 --> 00:55:58,572
your mind reached out,

733
00:55:58,594 --> 00:55:59,673
found me.

734
00:55:59,695 --> 00:56:01,140
We knew each other,

735
00:56:01,162 --> 00:56:05,679
shared each other's thoughts,
feelings, all our hopes,

736
00:56:06,200 --> 00:56:07,648
all our sorrows.

737
00:56:08,303 --> 00:56:09,683
When this...

738
00:56:09,705 --> 00:56:12,986
this power inside me came alive,

739
00:56:13,008 --> 00:56:15,221
I was so scared, Rose.

740
00:56:15,243 --> 00:56:17,758
I thought it was
going to burn me up,

741
00:56:17,779 --> 00:56:19,326
tear me apart.

742
00:56:19,348 --> 00:56:21,895
But then, I felt something.

743
00:56:21,917 --> 00:56:23,096
Like...

744
00:56:23,117 --> 00:56:25,432
Like the echo of my own soul.

745
00:56:25,954 --> 00:56:26,984
Me.

746
00:56:28,090 --> 00:56:29,503
You.

747
00:56:29,524 --> 00:56:31,538
I think I would have died
without you.

748
00:56:33,328 --> 00:56:35,642
And I would have died
without you.

749
00:56:38,165 --> 00:56:40,212
You see, Jericho,

750
00:56:40,234 --> 00:56:42,716
you don't need
a mother or a father...

751
00:56:45,874 --> 00:56:47,387
when you have me.

752
00:56:51,346 --> 00:56:54,528
<i>And what about the man
who calls himself your father?</i>

753
00:56:54,549 --> 00:56:56,195
<i>What about the Jackal?</i>

754
00:57:03,325 --> 00:57:05,305
Wintergreen, you there?

755
00:57:06,628 --> 00:57:07,974
<i>Always.</i>

756
00:57:23,578 --> 00:57:25,325
Hey, what about the boat?

757
00:57:29,317 --> 00:57:30,731
I stole it, anyway.

758
00:57:44,800 --> 00:57:45,912
Bring them in.

759
00:57:53,241 --> 00:57:55,589
Thank you, agents,
for volunteering.

760
00:57:55,610 --> 00:57:57,491
But we didn't volun...

761
00:57:59,681 --> 00:58:02,362
Agent Sanchez, step forward.

762
00:58:07,456 --> 00:58:08,802
<i>On your knees.</i>

763
00:58:11,593 --> 00:58:12,623
Now her.

764
00:58:15,430 --> 00:58:16,710
<i>Your weapon.</i>

765
00:58:22,971 --> 00:58:25,252
This is nothing
compared to what's coming.

766
00:58:25,273 --> 00:58:29,356
And if you can't do this,
all our plans are for nothing.

767
00:58:30,011 --> 00:58:31,041
<i>All right.</i>

768
00:58:33,982 --> 00:58:35,495
<i>Shoot him.</i>

769
00:58:48,964 --> 00:58:49,994
<i>I can't.</i>

770
00:58:54,302 --> 00:58:55,949
Why'd you stop?

771
00:58:55,971 --> 00:58:57,350
<i>It worked, didn't it?</i>

772
00:58:57,372 --> 00:58:59,386
<i>She would've killed him
on my command.</i>

773
00:58:59,407 --> 00:59:01,488
<i>Why lose a perfectly good agent?</i>

774
00:59:02,210 --> 00:59:03,723
Fine.

775
00:59:03,745 --> 00:59:06,626
Then let's have a show,
shall we?

776
00:59:30,239 --> 00:59:31,518
That's enough, Jericho.

777
00:59:40,916 --> 00:59:41,946
That's enough.

778
00:59:48,156 --> 00:59:49,186
Jericho, stop!

779
00:59:49,925 --> 00:59:50,955
Stop!

780
01:00:05,674 --> 01:00:07,153
<i>Oh, God! Oh, God!</i>

781
01:00:07,175 --> 01:00:09,556
<i>I'm sorry, Rose.
I don't know what happened!</i>

782
01:00:09,578 --> 01:00:11,524
<i>I couldn't control it! I...</i>

783
01:00:11,546 --> 01:00:13,827
Shh! It's my fault.

784
01:00:13,849 --> 01:00:16,897
I pushed you too far. Too fast.

785
01:00:16,918 --> 01:00:19,199
We'll go
a little slower tonight.

786
01:00:19,221 --> 01:00:22,535
<i>Tonight? But, can't we...</i>

787
01:00:22,557 --> 01:00:23,803
Tomorrow, then.

788
01:00:25,026 --> 01:00:26,673
And no more excuses.

789
01:00:33,535 --> 01:00:35,115
How did you get this?

790
01:00:35,136 --> 01:00:37,450
While you were blundering
into the H.I.V.E. Queen's trap,

791
01:00:37,472 --> 01:00:40,921
I was hacking
into their servers.

792
01:00:40,942 --> 01:00:43,924
Jericho.
That's what she called Joseph.

793
01:01:10,872 --> 01:01:13,753
They're turning our son
into a weapon of war.

794
01:01:13,775 --> 01:01:17,023
Remember what she said?
I'm a handgun, but Joseph's...

795
01:01:17,045 --> 01:01:18,392
A nuclear bomb.

796
01:01:18,413 --> 01:01:20,294
But not in the way you think.

797
01:01:20,316 --> 01:01:24,365
Those exercises are to help him
master his abilities, focus them.

798
01:01:24,387 --> 01:01:25,532
But the goal?

799
01:01:26,488 --> 01:01:28,702
A revolution from within.

800
01:01:28,723 --> 01:01:30,904
Imagine if you
controlled someone

801
01:01:30,926 --> 01:01:32,772
who could control
the minds of others.

802
01:01:32,794 --> 01:01:37,411
Presidents, prime ministers,
despots, kings.

803
01:01:37,432 --> 01:01:39,313
Mind-theft on a global scale.

804
01:01:39,335 --> 01:01:42,983
You could reshape the planet
without firing a single shot.

805
01:01:43,004 --> 01:01:47,554
And we've got ten days to figure
out what their first move is.

806
01:01:47,575 --> 01:01:49,589
And it's all because of her.

807
01:01:49,611 --> 01:01:52,258
She used Joseph.
Manipulated him.

808
01:01:55,750 --> 01:01:57,564
<i>You can do this.</i>

809
01:01:59,187 --> 01:02:01,134
<i>I know you're scared, Jericho,</i>

810
01:02:01,156 --> 01:02:02,836
<i>but I believe in you.</i>

811
01:02:02,857 --> 01:02:05,271
<i>As long as we have
each other, little brother,</i>

812
01:02:05,294 --> 01:02:08,442
<i>there's nothing
we can't accomplish.</i>

813
01:02:08,463 --> 01:02:10,710
<i>We're two parts of a whole.</i>

814
01:02:10,732 --> 01:02:12,612
<i>I'll never leave you.</i>

815
01:02:12,634 --> 01:02:15,248
<i>Never abandon you
the way they did.</i>

816
01:02:16,638 --> 01:02:18,585
<i>We're family.</i>

817
01:02:23,446 --> 01:02:26,526
Is that manipulation or love?

818
01:02:31,653 --> 01:02:34,567
Thanks, Addie.
I'll take it from here.

819
01:02:34,589 --> 01:02:36,036
The hell you will!

820
01:02:36,057 --> 01:02:38,772
You don't get to decide
what I do or don't do.

821
01:02:38,793 --> 01:02:41,375
You've risked enough.
This is my job.

822
01:02:41,397 --> 01:02:44,177
I lived with risk every
damn day we were married,

823
01:02:44,199 --> 01:02:48,114
only, I never knew it,
did I, Deathstroke?

824
01:02:48,136 --> 01:02:49,316
You never told me.

825
01:02:49,338 --> 01:02:51,684
Please, can we stop
dredging up the past?

826
01:02:51,706 --> 01:02:53,787
You know there's something else
you never told me.

827
01:02:54,576 --> 01:02:55,889
Why?

828
01:02:55,910 --> 01:02:59,159
Why did you choose
Deathstroke over us?

829
01:02:59,180 --> 01:03:01,429
A life of deceit and risk,
instead of...

830
01:03:01,450 --> 01:03:04,030
I didn't choose to be
one over the other, Addie.

831
01:03:04,052 --> 01:03:05,665
And I didn't choose to be this.

832
01:03:05,687 --> 01:03:07,100
There's always a choice.

833
01:03:07,122 --> 01:03:09,669
Those bastards made me this way

834
01:03:09,691 --> 01:03:11,539
with their damned experiment.

835
01:03:11,559 --> 01:03:13,307
And I did the best
I could with it.

836
01:03:13,329 --> 01:03:15,575
That was your best?

837
01:03:15,597 --> 01:03:18,078
A mercenary? A murderer?

838
01:03:18,867 --> 01:03:20,481
My father was a soldier.

839
01:03:20,503 --> 01:03:21,815
His father was a soldier.

840
01:03:21,836 --> 01:03:24,584
All I knew
was the military life.

841
01:03:24,606 --> 01:03:26,186
So I took that training and...

842
01:03:26,207 --> 01:03:28,556
Corrupted it. Spit on it.

843
01:03:28,576 --> 01:03:30,524
This world is filled with evil.

844
01:03:30,545 --> 01:03:33,026
On a scale you can't comprehend.

845
01:03:34,616 --> 01:03:36,663
Oh, I have some idea.

846
01:03:36,684 --> 01:03:41,267
Then you should understand that I just
did what we did when we served together.

847
01:03:41,290 --> 01:03:42,769
Took down the bad guys.

848
01:03:42,791 --> 01:03:45,071
Don't you dare compare the two.

849
01:03:52,233 --> 01:03:53,414
I...

850
01:03:53,436 --> 01:03:55,516
I tried to be the knight
Joseph believed I was.

851
01:03:55,538 --> 01:03:57,585
A knight?

852
01:03:57,605 --> 01:03:59,819
Is that what you think you are?

853
01:03:59,841 --> 01:04:03,557
Oh, my God, Slade,
are you that delusional?

854
01:04:03,578 --> 01:04:05,692
Joseph didn't need a knight.

855
01:04:05,713 --> 01:04:07,260
He needed a father.

856
01:04:07,283 --> 01:04:09,195
I needed a husband.

857
01:04:09,217 --> 01:04:14,234
What's so wrong inside you that
you preferred Deathstroke to us?

858
01:04:14,989 --> 01:04:16,769
My life as Deathstroke,

859
01:04:16,791 --> 01:04:18,738
it was separate
from my life with you.

860
01:04:18,760 --> 01:04:20,441
It had nothing to do with...

861
01:04:20,463 --> 01:04:21,941
You really don't see it?

862
01:04:21,963 --> 01:04:24,811
All these years
you've been compartmentalizing.

863
01:04:24,833 --> 01:04:27,714
Filing pieces of yourself
away in little boxes.

864
01:04:27,735 --> 01:04:30,317
Lying to yourself.
And to me.

865
01:04:31,606 --> 01:04:33,853
Thank you.

866
01:04:34,443 --> 01:04:36,357
For what?

867
01:04:36,378 --> 01:04:41,127
For reminding me why I've chosen to
remain a bachelor all these years.

868
01:04:41,149 --> 01:04:45,533
Now, are you two going to spend
the day at each other's throats,

869
01:04:45,554 --> 01:04:49,002
or are we going to save Joseph,
and perhaps the world?

870
01:05:14,916 --> 01:05:17,103
<i>The nation
has been rocked this morning</i>

871
01:05:17,118 --> 01:05:21,134
<i>by what appear to be a series of
coordinated terrorist attacks.</i>

872
01:05:21,156 --> 01:05:23,671
<i>Moments after a hijacked
Patriot Airlines flight</i>

873
01:05:23,691 --> 01:05:26,873
<i>was deliberately crashed
into the Golden Gate Bridge,</i>

874
01:05:26,895 --> 01:05:31,545
<i>a dozen armed men launched a mass
attack in New York Times Square.</i>

875
01:05:31,567 --> 01:05:32,879
<i>While in Washington,</i>

876
01:05:32,901 --> 01:05:35,048
<i>at least one bomb,
possibly more,</i>

877
01:05:35,069 --> 01:05:37,284
<i>tore through
the Capitol Building.</i>

878
01:05:37,306 --> 01:05:39,719
<i>No estimates yet
on total casualties,</i>

879
01:05:39,741 --> 01:05:44,023
<i>but it's clear that hundreds of
lives have been lost, perhaps more.</i>

880
01:05:44,045 --> 01:05:48,127
<i>The president, just returning from
the World Economic Forum in Davos,</i>

881
01:05:48,149 --> 01:05:50,129
<i>remains aboard Air Force One,</i>

882
01:05:50,151 --> 01:05:53,233
<i>while all other flights across
the nation have been grounded.</i>

883
01:05:54,356 --> 01:05:55,502
God damn it!

884
01:05:55,524 --> 01:05:58,838
I look like a weak fool,
circling around up here,

885
01:05:58,860 --> 01:06:00,106
afraid to land.

886
01:06:00,128 --> 01:06:02,041
It has nothing to
do with fear, sir.

887
01:06:02,063 --> 01:06:03,644
It's for your safety.

888
01:06:03,666 --> 01:06:06,012
Until we know the full
extent of the attacks...

889
01:06:06,034 --> 01:06:08,114
The nation needs
to be reassured!

890
01:06:08,136 --> 01:06:11,751
And the commander-in-chief
needs to be protected.

891
01:06:16,579 --> 01:06:18,157
Eerie, isn't it?

892
01:06:18,179 --> 01:06:20,126
We're the only plane in the sky.

893
01:06:24,919 --> 01:06:27,100
At least, we're supposed to be.

894
01:06:37,065 --> 01:06:39,879
Our attacks were
the perfect distraction.

895
01:06:39,901 --> 01:06:42,383
The entire country is in chaos.

896
01:06:42,404 --> 01:06:44,385
People are hiding away
in their little holes

897
01:06:44,406 --> 01:06:46,420
like the frightened rabbits
they are.

898
01:06:47,208 --> 01:06:50,023
And there he sits, all alone.

899
01:06:51,280 --> 01:06:55,562
A fat, ripe fruit,
ready for the picking.

900
01:06:55,584 --> 01:06:59,999
Without you, child,
none of this would be possible.

901
01:07:00,021 --> 01:07:02,235
If I've pleased you, sir,
then...

902
01:07:02,258 --> 01:07:04,738
You've more than pleased me.

903
01:07:04,759 --> 01:07:06,740
You've given me the world.

904
01:07:06,794 --> 01:07:08,642
Are you ready, son?

905
01:07:08,664 --> 01:07:10,377
<i>I... I think so.</i>

906
01:07:10,399 --> 01:07:12,245
You think?

907
01:07:12,268 --> 01:07:13,314
<i>I am, sir.</i>

908
01:07:13,935 --> 01:07:15,382
We'll swarm them.

909
01:07:15,404 --> 01:07:16,983
Confuse and terrify them.

910
01:07:17,005 --> 01:07:18,285
And when they're close enough,

911
01:07:18,307 --> 01:07:21,322
you'll use
your astonishing gift.

912
01:07:21,343 --> 01:07:24,057
And our little puppet
will return to Washington.

913
01:07:24,078 --> 01:07:26,025
Declare martial law.

914
01:07:26,047 --> 01:07:29,396
The most powerful nation on Earth
will be in H.I.V.E.'s control and...

915
01:07:29,418 --> 01:07:30,863
And we

916
01:07:30,885 --> 01:07:33,434
will be in control of H.I.V.E.

917
01:07:33,821 --> 01:07:35,034
What?

918
01:07:35,056 --> 01:07:36,470
Now, Jericho!

919
01:07:44,032 --> 01:07:46,112
Rose?

920
01:07:46,134 --> 01:07:48,848
I've waited a long time
for this.

921
01:07:57,979 --> 01:08:00,661
You trained him well.

922
01:08:00,683 --> 01:08:02,161
Better than I knew.

923
01:08:02,183 --> 01:08:03,764
And all of this for what?

924
01:08:03,786 --> 01:08:05,599
Vengeance?
A righteous killing?

925
01:08:05,621 --> 01:08:09,803
You manipulated me from the first
moment you stepped into my life.

926
01:08:09,824 --> 01:08:12,840
Did you think I didn't know
what you were even then?

927
01:08:12,860 --> 01:08:15,908
I was a father to you.
I trained you.

928
01:08:15,930 --> 01:08:17,910
Helped you master those powers.

929
01:08:17,932 --> 01:08:19,413
A father?

930
01:08:19,435 --> 01:08:22,949
You used a lonely,
grief-stricken girl.

931
01:08:22,970 --> 01:08:25,586
But I wasn't as alone
as you believed.

932
01:08:25,607 --> 01:08:28,555
I had my brother, in here.

933
01:08:28,577 --> 01:08:31,625
Long before I ever
told you about him.

934
01:08:31,647 --> 01:08:35,128
And I knew what you did to him.

935
01:08:35,149 --> 01:08:38,030
I made you a queen.

936
01:08:38,052 --> 01:08:41,033
And now that queen
is taking your throne.

937
01:08:41,055 --> 01:08:43,871
H.I.V.E. won't use us again.

938
01:08:43,891 --> 01:08:47,508
No one will ever use us,
hurt us, again.

939
01:08:48,129 --> 01:08:50,209
We have the power.

940
01:08:50,231 --> 01:08:54,080
And what will you do
with all that power, Rose?

941
01:08:55,237 --> 01:08:58,184
I'll start by making you pay
for what you did.

942
01:08:58,206 --> 01:09:00,421
But not with your life.

943
01:09:00,442 --> 01:09:01,954
With your mind.

944
01:09:01,976 --> 01:09:04,023
Take him! Become him!

945
01:09:21,497 --> 01:09:24,478
Did you really think
I'd unleash a weapon like you

946
01:09:24,500 --> 01:09:26,780
without providing
myself protection?

947
01:09:26,802 --> 01:09:30,451
Took my best technicians eight months
to come up with psychic dampers

948
01:09:30,472 --> 01:09:33,487
capable of absorbing
your psionic powers,

949
01:09:33,509 --> 01:09:36,956
and hurling them back
in your astonished face.

950
01:09:42,551 --> 01:09:44,498
You knew?

951
01:09:44,520 --> 01:09:46,098
I suspected.

952
01:09:46,120 --> 01:09:49,536
After all, a guttersnipe
like you can't be trusted.

953
01:09:54,730 --> 01:09:55,943
Jericho.

954
01:09:55,963 --> 01:09:57,076
Jericho?

955
01:10:04,172 --> 01:10:08,355
You should know, Rose,
that family will always disappoint you.

956
01:10:08,377 --> 01:10:11,825
Denied the president's mind,
we'll have to take his body.

957
01:10:11,847 --> 01:10:14,628
I enjoy a good old-fashioned
kidnapping, don't you?

958
01:10:15,617 --> 01:10:18,465
Initiate Plan Jericho Two.
On my...

959
01:10:18,487 --> 01:10:20,340
Sir, another plane, heading our way.

960
01:10:20,355 --> 01:10:22,034
Who the hell could it...

961
01:10:22,957 --> 01:10:24,438
Deathstroke.

962
01:10:38,105 --> 01:10:39,553
<i>We warned them.</i>

963
01:10:40,409 --> 01:10:42,389
Why didn't they listen?

964
01:10:42,411 --> 01:10:45,365
By the time our contacts got through to
the people who could make a difference,

965
01:10:45,380 --> 01:10:48,094
it was just too late.

966
01:10:48,115 --> 01:10:50,497
But we'll damn sure
make a difference here.

967
01:10:52,521 --> 01:10:54,701
These energy readings
are extraordinary.

968
01:10:54,723 --> 01:10:57,538
It's got to be Joseph.
He's in the lead plane.

969
01:10:57,559 --> 01:11:00,507
You gonna be okay
all alone, Grandpa?

970
01:11:00,529 --> 01:11:02,643
<i>Oy, behave yourself.</i>

971
01:11:02,664 --> 01:11:04,318
<i>Have you looked in the mirror
lately, you old bag of wind?</i>

972
01:11:04,333 --> 01:11:05,946
<i>I've got this, Slade.</i>

973
01:11:05,968 --> 01:11:07,246
You always do.

974
01:11:11,707 --> 01:11:13,720
You're not talking me
out of this.

975
01:11:13,742 --> 01:11:15,422
I wouldn't dream of it.

976
01:11:15,444 --> 01:11:18,157
You're the finest commanding
officer I've ever served under.

977
01:11:18,179 --> 01:11:21,461
And you get extra points
since I've seen you naked.

978
01:11:22,951 --> 01:11:24,464
Fuck you.

979
01:11:40,669 --> 01:11:42,081
How did they know?

980
01:11:42,103 --> 01:11:43,983
They're here now.
And maybe that's for the best.

981
01:11:45,807 --> 01:11:49,456
Wilson's brats may have betrayed
me and ruined my careful planning.

982
01:11:49,478 --> 01:11:52,392
But now their father
can have a front-row seat

983
01:11:52,414 --> 01:11:54,294
when his children die.

984
01:12:33,322 --> 01:12:34,322
What's happening?

985
01:12:44,933 --> 01:12:45,963
Kill them.

986
01:13:17,899 --> 01:13:19,646
Bravo, Rose.

987
01:13:20,167 --> 01:13:21,381
Bravo.

988
01:13:54,136 --> 01:13:55,816
Not bad for an old dog.

989
01:14:12,287 --> 01:14:14,735
No! No, no, no!

990
01:14:27,234 --> 01:14:29,983
<i>Air Force
One, prepare to be boarded.</i>

991
01:14:53,929 --> 01:14:56,943
You just saved the President
of the United States.

992
01:14:56,965 --> 01:14:58,445
Damn right I did.

993
01:15:04,606 --> 01:15:06,953
It appears we were expected.

994
01:15:20,388 --> 01:15:21,668
Joseph!

995
01:15:27,529 --> 01:15:29,009
So, tell me, Wilson.

996
01:15:29,765 --> 01:15:32,512
Which one do I murder first?

997
01:15:32,534 --> 01:15:35,182
The girl whose mother
you used for your own pleasure

998
01:15:35,203 --> 01:15:37,584
and then so casually threw away?

999
01:15:37,606 --> 01:15:40,420
Or the boy
you so easily abandoned?

1000
01:15:40,442 --> 01:15:43,390
Spare me the litany
of my sins, Jackal.

1001
01:15:43,411 --> 01:15:45,158
I know them well enough.

1002
01:15:45,180 --> 01:15:48,028
Of course. You're not
the only sinner here.

1003
01:15:48,049 --> 01:15:50,931
Take our dear friend Rose,
for instance.

1004
01:15:50,952 --> 01:15:53,800
She's been manipulating
her brother for years.

1005
01:15:53,822 --> 01:15:57,771
Poisoning his mind
against you and Adeline.

1006
01:15:57,793 --> 01:16:01,309
Making sure
his only loyalty was to her.

1007
01:16:01,363 --> 01:16:05,378
I told him the truth.
I love Jericho.

1008
01:16:05,400 --> 01:16:08,648
And what's love but another
way to control people?

1009
01:16:09,070 --> 01:16:10,100
No.

1010
01:16:12,440 --> 01:16:16,056
What you did to him was no
different from what I did to you.

1011
01:16:16,077 --> 01:16:17,624
No.

1012
01:16:17,646 --> 01:16:19,893
God, no!

1013
01:16:19,915 --> 01:16:22,829
It's not the same, Rose.
You're not the same.

1014
01:16:24,219 --> 01:16:27,301
But I did use him. I...

1015
01:16:27,322 --> 01:16:30,036
I didn't mean to, but I did.

1016
01:16:30,058 --> 01:16:33,740
Just because love isn't perfect,
doesn't mean it isn't real.

1017
01:16:33,762 --> 01:16:36,476
You were there for him,
when I wasn't.

1018
01:16:36,498 --> 01:16:38,979
Not for him.
Not for you.

1019
01:16:42,871 --> 01:16:46,486
Hardly the time or
place for family therapy.

1020
01:16:49,110 --> 01:16:51,725
Let them go.

1021
01:16:54,182 --> 01:16:56,196
Say "please."

1022
01:16:56,218 --> 01:16:59,099
Please.
They've suffered enough.

1023
01:16:59,120 --> 01:17:01,001
Then I'll end their suffering.

1024
01:17:03,091 --> 01:17:05,005
You fucking monster.

1025
01:17:06,661 --> 01:17:08,708
I told you years ago, Wilson.

1026
01:17:09,531 --> 01:17:11,211
We're two of a kind.

1027
01:17:11,233 --> 01:17:13,113
Get the hell away from my kids!

1028
01:17:38,261 --> 01:17:41,274
I've performed several
major upgrades to this armor

1029
01:17:41,297 --> 01:17:43,009
since our last battle.

1030
01:17:43,031 --> 01:17:44,061
And, now,

1031
01:17:45,200 --> 01:17:46,846
I'm unstoppable!

1032
01:18:07,323 --> 01:18:09,502
Not bad.

1033
01:18:36,184 --> 01:18:37,170
Thank you.

1034
01:18:37,185 --> 01:18:38,631
We've got to help him.

1035
01:18:45,794 --> 01:18:46,824
Jericho.

1036
01:18:48,163 --> 01:18:50,710
Jericho. Joseph.

1037
01:18:50,732 --> 01:18:52,612
I'm so sorry.

1038
01:18:52,634 --> 01:18:55,282
- I never meant to-
<i>- I know. I...</i>

1039
01:18:56,405 --> 01:18:58,051
<i>Mom?</i>

1040
01:18:58,073 --> 01:18:59,686
Hey, little soldier.

1041
01:19:19,894 --> 01:19:21,741
All these years, Jackal...

1042
01:19:22,230 --> 01:19:24,611
Why? Why me?

1043
01:19:25,334 --> 01:19:27,047
Why my children?

1044
01:19:27,068 --> 01:19:30,583
Do you think you were the only
man to ever have a daughter?

1045
01:20:03,738 --> 01:20:05,752
She was your...

1046
01:20:05,774 --> 01:20:07,854
Yes, she was!

1047
01:20:11,514 --> 01:20:13,660
And now, I'll take from you

1048
01:20:13,681 --> 01:20:15,962
what you took from me.

1049
01:20:32,133 --> 01:20:33,246
No!

1050
01:20:44,612 --> 01:20:45,992
Slade!

1051
01:20:57,959 --> 01:20:59,706
<i>You were right, Addie.</i>

1052
01:21:01,663 --> 01:21:06,313
<i>All these years I've been filing
pieces of myself away in little boxes.</i>

1053
01:21:06,335 --> 01:21:08,214
<i>Lying to myself.</i>

1054
01:21:08,237 --> 01:21:09,849
<i>And to you.</i>

1055
01:21:09,871 --> 01:21:12,286
<i>It was the only way
I knew how to survive.</i>

1056
01:21:13,576 --> 01:21:15,155
<i>I'm not a knight, my love.</i>

1057
01:21:17,446 --> 01:21:18,858
<i>I never was.</i>

1058
01:21:21,350 --> 01:21:26,099
<i>But maybe now I can be
the man you always needed.</i>

1059
01:21:29,891 --> 01:21:31,871
- Can you?
- I can try.

1060
01:21:38,967 --> 01:21:40,780
How long can you keep it there?

1061
01:21:40,802 --> 01:21:42,550
<i>As long as I have to.</i>

1062
01:21:42,571 --> 01:21:44,984
<i>I'm not losing you again.</i>

1063
01:21:47,576 --> 01:21:49,088
I'll get us down fast.

1064
01:22:00,121 --> 01:22:01,968
Wintergreen,
can you see them?

1065
01:22:03,758 --> 01:22:05,271
No, I...

1066
01:22:05,294 --> 01:22:07,273
Wait! There!

1067
01:22:07,296 --> 01:22:10,143
You get to ground.
I'll try to reach Slade.

1068
01:22:15,136 --> 01:22:16,883
This has been fun, Wilson.

1069
01:22:20,975 --> 01:22:23,557
But it's time to
say our good-byes.

1070
01:22:23,579 --> 01:22:26,092
This isn't gonna
end well for you.

1071
01:22:30,084 --> 01:22:32,399
Not for you either, asshole.

1072
01:22:33,721 --> 01:22:35,735
What?

1073
01:22:35,757 --> 01:22:38,472
<i>Joseph, I love you.</i>

1074
01:22:43,499 --> 01:22:44,485
Slade!

1075
01:22:44,500 --> 01:22:45,745
<i>Papa!</i>

1076
01:22:54,610 --> 01:22:59,526
<i>"The land was filled with
dragons and the people were afraid."</i>

1077
01:22:59,548 --> 01:23:02,363
<i>But the Shining Knight
came riding forth</i>

1078
01:23:02,384 --> 01:23:05,765
<i>to protect both man and maid.</i>

1079
01:23:05,787 --> 01:23:07,900
<i>He faced the fiercest creatures</i>

1080
01:23:07,922 --> 01:23:10,437
<i>that the world had ever known.</i>

1081
01:23:10,459 --> 01:23:13,474
<i>And he did it all to save us.</i>

1082
01:23:13,495 --> 01:23:15,241
<i>"For the knight was not alone."</i>

1083
01:23:15,264 --> 01:23:18,412
<i>Oh, how he loved reading
that book to you.</i>

1084
01:23:19,801 --> 01:23:21,548
<i>That...</i>

1085
01:23:21,570 --> 01:23:23,149
<i>That was a long time ago.</i>

1086
01:23:26,675 --> 01:23:28,087
<i>The past is dead.</i>

1087
01:23:35,551 --> 01:23:36,896
He needs time.

1088
01:23:37,620 --> 01:23:39,400
We all need time.

1089
01:23:39,421 --> 01:23:42,869
Do you think he survived?

1090
01:23:42,890 --> 01:23:45,572
Not even he could
have survived that.

1091
01:23:53,167 --> 01:23:54,548
I'll be leaving tomorrow.

1092
01:23:55,337 --> 01:23:56,383
And going where?

1093
01:23:59,742 --> 01:24:01,988
You stay as long as you need to.

1094
01:24:02,010 --> 01:24:03,590
We're family now.

1095
01:24:03,612 --> 01:24:08,261
Dysfunctional as
hell, but we're family.

1096
01:24:33,542 --> 01:24:36,357
<i>"The land was filled
with dragons,"</i>

1097
01:24:36,378 --> 01:24:39,192
<i>and the people were afraid.</i>

1098
01:24:39,213 --> 01:24:42,061
<i>But the Shining Knight
came riding forth</i>

1099
01:24:42,083 --> 01:24:45,399
<i>to protect both man and maid.</i>

1100
01:24:45,421 --> 01:24:47,501
<i>He faced the fiercest creatures</i>

1101
01:24:47,523 --> 01:24:49,403
<i>that the world had ever known.</i>

1102
01:24:51,159 --> 01:24:53,374
<i>And he did it all to save us.</i>

1103
01:24:54,296 --> 01:24:56,610
<i>For the Knight was not alone.</i>

1104
01:24:57,932 --> 01:25:00,012
<i>And when his work was done,</i>

1105
01:25:01,270 --> 01:25:03,283
<i>the dragons were no more.</i>

1106
01:25:04,340 --> 01:25:06,919
<i>And so the Knight rode on</i>

1107
01:25:07,842 --> 01:25:09,556
<i>into legend,</i>

1108
01:25:09,578 --> 01:25:11,458
<i>"into lore."</i>

1109
